Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian Castlegar , BC Description Under the direction of the College Librarian, and working collegially with other Library staff, the casual Librarian is responsible for providing reference and instructional services for students and faculty, and developing the collection in assigned subject areas. As a small academic library, all librarians are expected to be generalists and be able to provide support for other librarians in their absence.Main Duties and ResponsibilitiesProvides Library services to students and staff by:Developing and conducting instructional classes for research skills and information literacy;Providing reference services for students and faculty as needed;Developing the collection through the selection of new material and weeding of older material in designated subject areas;Creating and maintaining supplemental material such as citation style guides, research workbooks and subject guides;Performs other duties as assignedSkills, Knowledge and AbilitiesExcellent interpersonal and communication skillsExpertise with using major research databasesAbility to effectively work with the various information technologies used in the LibraryAbility to work with and contribute to a teamExcellent understanding of current trends in library and information scienceStrong services commitmentEducation and ExperienceA Master’s degree in Library and Information Science (MLS or MLIS) from an ALA-accredited institutionMinimum 1-year experience working as a Librarian in an academic environmentThis is a short-term full-time position commencing August 21, 2023 and ending December 22, 2023, or until the return of the incumbent with the possibility of extension. Salary and benefits are in accordance with the Selkirk College Faculty Association Collective Agreement. For complete details and information on how to apply visit: https://careers.selkirk.ca/vacancy/librarian-36461... Compensation $2,369.08 - $3,806.85 bi-weekly (at 100% appointment) based on qualifications and experience Closes: 30 June, 2023 Selkirk College Castlegar , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
