Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Research Services Librarian Winnipeg , MB Description Library and Academic ServicesApplicants are to clearly demonstrate how they satisfy the selection criteria in their written submissions and must identify the competition number when submitting their application.An eligibility list may be created for similar casual, part-time, full-time, and term positionsDUTIESThe Research Services Librarian (RSL) will be Library and Academic Services’ (LAS) sole research specialist, developing programs, services, and partnerships in support of the information and research needs of Red River College Polytechnic faculty, students, and researchers. Reporting to the Manager, Information and Program Delivery (I&amp;PD) the RSL’s key duties will include creating, delivering, and assessing the programs, resources, and training that support the College’s research endeavors. The incumbent will serve on internal and external committees to provide expert level guidance; advise on research design and methodology, information sources, and research skills; and support scholarly communication for researchers at RRC Polytech. The RSL will participate in planning and direction setting for LAS to ensure research services, resources, and programs align with the priorities of the College. Other duties include working closely with the Manger, I&amp;PD to direct the work of Library Technicians for research related projects and initiatives; and provide service desk and library instruction supportREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS Master of Library and Information Sciences from an ALA accredited institute; an equivalent combination of education and experience may be considered Experience effectively supporting research in a post-secondary institute Experience supporting scholarly communication and understanding of how libraries can support researchers through the scholarly communication lifecycle Knowledge of the Canadian Tri-Agencies and the role of libraries within this context Excellent communication skills, including verbal, written, and listening skills Experience working with, leading, and persuading others Ability to develop positive and productive working relationships across units Excellent instruction and presentation skills Experience developing, implementing, and leading library services Effective analytical, critical thinking, and problem-solving skills with the ability to act on sound judgement Ability to work independently and in a team environment Understanding of project and change management principles that promote a forward-thinking and proactive culture Commitment to patron service and improving the library user experience Willingness to stay up to date with library trends Experience building a respectful workplace culture that promotes diversity, learning and continuous improvementCONDITIONS OF EMPLOYMENTApplicants must be legally entitled to work in CanadaThis position may be required to work evenings and/or weekendsPOSITION LOCATION Notre Dame Campus (Winnipeg, MB)POSITION TYPE Full-Time Position AvailableAPPLY ONLINE AT rrc.ca/careersRRC Polytech is a leader in applied learning and innovation. Our talented team of employees is passionate about education, innovation and student success. We offer competitive salaries, extensive benefits and the opportunity for personal and professional growth in a rewarding career.At RRC Polytech we are committed to fostering an inclusive environment, where all employees and students feel valued, respected and supported. We aspire to have a workforce that is representative of the diversity within our communities, and welcome applications from women, Indigenous Peoples, persons with disabilities, racialized persons, persons of the 2SLGBTQIA+ community and others who may contribute to the further diversification of ideas. All qualified candidates are encouraged to apply; however, Canadians and permanent residents will be given priority.If you require this information in an alternate format, please contact humanresources@rrc.ca. Compensation $57,780 - $79,057 per annum Closes: 27 June, 2023 Red River College Polytechnic Winnipeg , MB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
