Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Circulation Technician Toronto , ON Description Keeping Ontario’s Legislative Assembly running smoothly takes many talented people, doing many different jobs—from camera operators and committee clerks, to purchasing officers and researchers. The Office of the Assembly is dedicated to serving Ontario’s Parliament.Together, we provide non-partisan administrative and procedural services to all MPPs, as well as operational support for the daily activities of the Legislative Assembly of Ontario. Our success is determined by the strength and diversity of our staff and by supporting our core values: integrity, inclusiveness, collaboration and excellence.Circulation Technician Can you provide excellent service while following library procedures? Can you work both independently and collaboratively as part of the team? The Legislative Assembly of Ontario, located in Toronto, seeks a Circulation Technician, to join the Circulation and News Team, within the Legislative Library Branch. You will play a significant role as the first impression clients will have of the Branch by receiving their calls, greeting visitors, and providing exceptional customer service to Members of the Provincial Parliament (MPPs), officers and staff of the Assembly. You will also support the branch by playing a role in building the Library’s collection of resources (e.g. press releases) archiving them to the Library’s digital repository, processing for documents shelving, and/or making them discoverable through the online catalogue.What You’ll DoYou’ll act with integrity to:Interact with MPPs and their staff, retrieving materials, and handling circulation transactions using an integrated library system (ILS)Provide basic research assistance in a fast-paced environment to clients and reference support to Research Librarians and Research Officers, performing searches in print and electronic news sources such as Lexis Nexis, ProQuest, etc. Assist with stack maintenance and shelving, update loose-leaf services, and process interlibrary loansAssist with receiving, check-in and processing of Parliamentary and Sessional Papers, and Election Finance materialAssist with pickup and delivery to/from other libraries, local bookstores or organizationsDownload publications (e.g. party press release)from the internet and archive to the library’s digital repository, following the Library’s collection policyCreate original descriptive cataloguing records for publications (e.g. party press releases)following international standards, such as RDA and MARC 21, and in-house policiesOffer suggestions related to collection management, including recommended discards of little-used and outdated material.You’ll support our collaboration as you:Are able to work both independently and collaboratively in a well-established team environmentAre a highly motivated self-starter with excellent interpersonal skills, the ability to work independently or in a team and the flexibility and other skills needed to serve a client group with frequently changing priorities and tight deadlinesMay be required to undertake occasional assignments outside the Circulation &amp; News Services unit in addition to your primary responsibilities, such as collaborating with others on branch/division teams or special projectsHow You Qualify You demonstrate excellence through your: Completion of a college diploma (a recognized library techniques program or equivalent is preferred) and up to 2 year of prior related /on-the-job experience.Demonstrated advanced reading comprehension, attention to detail, strong organizational skills, flexibility, and demonstrated experience working under pressureProficiency in relevant computer technology systems and software applications Service orientation, well-developed communication, organizational, analytical and interpersonal skills, demonstrated experience working under pressure, flexibility to multi-task in response to clients’ changing priorities and deadlinesEnthusiasm and motivation, ability to work independently and collaboratively as part of the team to solve problems, share and communicate knowledgeIf you join our team, you can expect: Comprehensive benefits and pension package Access to an employee and family assistance program A dynamic work environmentTo work with a team of dedicated professionalsTo be encouraged and supported to grow your career through training and developmentLong Service Recognition AwardsFlexible workplace options may be available Salary Range: $54,809 to $74,538 per annum File No.: LA-2023-67 Closing Date: June 22, 2023If you share our values and are interested in this position, please visit us at www.ola.org and select Careers for more details.The Legislative Assembly of Ontario embraces diversity and as an equal opportunity employer is committed to creating an inclusive workplace while establishing a diversified qualified workforce. If you require accommodation in order to participate in the recruitment process, please email your contact information to hr@ola.org for follow-up.While we appreciate your interest in obtaining employment with the Legislative Assembly of Ontario, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $54,809.00 - $74,538.00 per annum Closes: 22 June, 2023 Legislative Assembly of Ontario Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
