Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician – Circulation and Serials Winnipeg , MB Description The Library Technician – Circulation and Serials oversees all circulation functions, maintains journal records and subscriptions, processes library donations, and functions as member of library team to provide excellent library services to students, faculty, and other library patrons. SUPERVISORY FUNCTIONS: Does not have full supervisory responsibilities but has a lead hand type of function assigning tasks and providing direction to part-time Library Assistants and/or volunteers. ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS OF THE JOB/ROLES AND RESPONSIBILITIES: Oversee all circulation functions including patron record maintenance, processing fines and billing patrons, cash transactions and deposits Document circulation policies and proceduresProvide patron assistance including answering inquiries, checking books out, verifying book status, research support, etc.Co-ordinate creation and updating of course and assignment pathfindersMaintain reserves collectionTrain and oversee work of part time Library Assistants and volunteersCoordinate stacks maintenance, including shelving, shelf reading, and cleaningInitiate and renew journal subscriptions; check in journals; order missing back issues Maintain journal records including up to date listings and electronic Table of Contents alerts to faculty and staffRecord and process in-kind donations; request receipts from Advancement departmentOrder office and library suppliesAssist with bulletin board and book displays, with maintenance of library website and with other general library dutiesIntroduce patrons to the John Fairbank Memorial Library through tours, orientations, and workshopsPost-secondary two-year diploma in Library and Information TechnologyProficient in basic library procedures, cataloguing procedures, bibliographic verification, Windows operating system, MS Office, AACR2r, MARC, LCSH, and LC shelving rulesPossess strong interpersonal skills and a commitment to high standards of customer service Be able to resolve problems creatively and effectively and to work with limited supervisionHave demonstrated strengths in area of research and computer skills, including use of online databases QUALIFICATIONS 1. Required Satisfactory criminal record check Fully supportive of the integration of faith and learning in a Christian university-level setting and a commitment to the Mission of Booth University College Ability to integrate your Christian faith within the workplacePost-secondary two-year diploma in Library and Information TechnologyProficient in basic library procedures, cataloguing procedures, bibliographic verification, Windows operating system, MS Office, AACR2r, MARC, LCSH, and LC shelving rulesPossess strong interpersonal skills and a commitment to high standards of customer service Be able to resolve problems creatively and effectively and to work with limited supervisionHave demonstrated strengths in area of research and computer skills, including use of online databases2. Assets (Preferred Qualifications) Familiarity with maintaining and updating webpages This is a full-time position with 37.5 hours per week. In addition to the compensation package, we also provide a benefits package that includes health, dental, and other group benefits, vacation and sick leave, RRSP, and a tuition bursary program. Booth University College offers a stimulating university college environment, a mission-driven purpose, and the opportunity to contribute to change as Booth UC moves forward on its commitment to its mission: Education for a Better World. Application Instructions Applications may be submitted in confidence to Human Resources; Booth University College by email: BoothUC.Careers@boothuc.ca. Applications must include a cover letter. In the letter describe why you want to work at Booth University College. Also, please detail what key strengths you bring to this position. All qualified candidates are encouraged to apply however, in accordance with Canadian Immigration requirements, Canadians and permanent residents will be given priority. Accommodations are available upon request throughout the recruitment process. About Booth University College Booth UC is a Christian university college located in Winnipeg, Manitoba (Canada) and rooted in The Salvation Army’s history of meeting the needs of the most vulnerable in society. As an open-enrollment institution, we welcome students from many different backgrounds, cultures, and countries. Deeply committed to social justice, we blend Christian faith and rigorous scholarship with a passion for service. Our approach to learning is anchored in academic excellence and based on a vision of social justice, hope, and mercy for all. We are committed to our mission: Education for a Better World. This is described in our mission statement: William and Catherine Booth University College, a Christian university college rooted in The Salvation Army’s Wesleyan theological tradition, brings together Christian faith, rigorous scholarship, and a passion for service. The University College educates students to understand the complexities of our world, to develop the knowledge and skills necessary to be active contributors to society, and to know how the Christian faith compels them to bring hope, social justice, and mercy into our world. Compensation Between $21.50 to $23.50 per hour, depending on skills and experience Closes: 5 July, 2023 Booth University College (John Fairbank Memorial Library) Winnipeg , MB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
