Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Digital Literacy Programmer Kitchener , ON Description Digital Literacy ProgrammerJune 14, 2023Digital Literacy Full-time $53,379 – $61,905 Day, Evening and Weekend Shifts Who we are Kitchener Public Library welcomes our community to engaging spaces where people connect, ideas flourish and lives are transformed. Our values are a reflection of who we are and what we strive for as a library. The principles of equity, inclusion and belonging are present in all that we do. Everything from our spaces to our services is designed to value diversity, foster belonging and respect individual needs. What we offer Comprehensive benefits Reliable pensionLearning and development Innovative culture Paid time-off What you will do The Digital Literacy Programmer will develop and deliver creative and innovative digital literacy programs that support the community. The position holder inspires collaboration between departments and acts as a resource to assist staff system wide with all digital programming needs. Delivers a high level of customer service and support at Central Library. Service points include Heffner Studio, Information Services, Children’s and Teen Services, Welcome Desk and Community Library locations. Develops and delivers digital literacy programming and initiatives across the library system. Provides instruction and training to customers and staff on the use of Digital Maker Tools, 3D printers, scanners, projectors, project peripherals, iMacs etc., including troubleshooting hardware and navigating software. What you bring Post-secondary degree 1 year of experience teaching or instructing a wide range of audiences (children, teen, adult) 1 year of library experience How to apply If you are interested in this position, please send your résumé and application form to Human Resources via resumes@kpl.org by Friday, June 23, 2023. Please quote Digital Literacy Programmer in the subject line. To print a copy of our application form, go to kpl.org/jobs Accommodations are available upon request for applicants with a disability. Please contact Human Resources staff by phone 519-743-0271 ext. 276 or TTY 1-877-614-4832, or by email hr@kpl.org Compensation $53,379 - $61,905 Closes: 23 June, 2023 Kitchener Public Library Kitchener , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
