Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Supervisor, Library Branches Keswick , ON Description Supervisor, Library Branches (Posting #2023.71) Department: Georgina Public Library Location: Georgina – All Branches Status: Permanent, Full Time Number of Positions: 1 Salary: $75,741 to $89,125 per annum Date Posted: June 13, 2023 Date Closing: July 4, 2023 Come work with us! Employment with Georgina Public Library offers an opportunity to make a positive difference in our community. We are a progressive, forward-thinking organization focused on continuous improvement, innovation and providing exceptional customer service. We offer a collaborative team environment and an excellent place to take charge of your career. Position Purpose The Supervisor, Library Branches is an integral member of the Georgina Public Library team and is responsible for the oversight of the day-to-day operations of library branches, including public service, staff training, scheduling, safety and security, and maintenance of facilities and equipment, with the goal of cultivating an environment that strives for customer service excellence in a rapidly changing environment. As a regular presence in each branch, the Supervisor, Library Branches will offer service continuity for the community and support for library staff in a way that meets the strategic direction set forth by the GPL Board. For full details, please see attached job description Minimum Qualifications Library Technician’s Diploma, Business Administration diploma, or diploma in another relevant discipline. 2 years previous library experience, including 6 months in a Library Assistant position or equivalent. 6 months supervisory experience, preferably in a unionized environment. Thorough knowledge of library policies, procedures, practices, and relevant legislation. Ability to act as customer service champion. Excellent public relations, problem solving, interpersonal, and organizational skills. Strong leadership and communication skills. Ability to deal effectively with staff through coaching and training. Skill and efficiency in the use of computers and related technologies, including basic proficiency in Excel. Ability to teach others in a patient manner. High ethics and values. Flexibility to work a variety of shifts, including evenings and weekends. Requirement to travel to various locations. Valid Class 'G' Driver's license and reliable vehicle to use on corporate business. Satisfactory Vulnerable Sector Screening. How to apply Qualified applicants are invited to submit a resume and cover letter, identifying the Job Title and Job ID#. Please apply by visiting the www.georgina.ca/careers no later than 11:59 pm on the closing date. The assessment process may include a practical test and/or interview. Committed to diversity and a barrier-free environment The Town of Georgina is an equal opportunity employer and we will accommodate the needs of applicants under the Ontario Human Rights Code and the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA) throughout all stages of the recruitment and selection process. Please advise the Human Resources Office to ensure your accessibility needs are accommodated. We thank all candidates for their interest, however only those being considered will be contacted. Personal information collected will be used in accordance with the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act for the purpose of candidate selection. Further information concerning the collection of personal information should be directed to the Human Resources Manager, Town of Georgina, 26557 Civic Centre Road, Keswick, ON L4P 3G1 (905) 476-4301 JOB DESCRIPTION: Supervisor, Library Branches Reports to:Manager, Library Customer Experience Direct Reports:Library Students Indirect Reports: May provide occasional guidance, training/assistance to Library Clerks, Library Assistants, Circulation Coordinators, and volunteers Position Purpose The Supervisor, Library Branches is an integral member of the Georgina Public Library team and is responsible for the oversight of the day-to-day operations of library branches, including public service, staff training, scheduling, safety and security, and maintenance of facilities and equipment, with the goal of cultivating an environment that strives for customer service excellence in a rapidly changing environment. As a regular presence in each branch, the Supervisor, Library Branches will offer service continuity for the community and support for library staff in a way that meets the strategic direction set forth by the GPL Board. Responsibilities Supervises library activities by scheduling, coordinating, implementing, and evaluating staffing to ensure consistent levels of service across the library system.Oversees training, supervision, and evaluation of student employees. Provides team leadership: leads, empowers, coaches, fosters collaborative work environment; models enthusiasm and commitment; promotes teamwork; provides clear direction and effective communication; mediates conflict. Performs personnel monitoring: recognizes accomplishments; oversees and tracks staff training and orientation; establishes performance expectations; ensures appropriate tools are available and communicates needs to manager. Ensures efficient library operations and compliance with established policies and procedures, and that employees are well informed and trained in/on policies, services, operations, programs, and events.Collaborates with library leadership to develop and implement goals, policies, and procedures. Coordinates activities and programs with staff.Acts as Customer Service Champion: models exemplary customer service skills; demonstrably applies knowledge of organizational mission, values, policies, procedures, collections, programs, services, and resources; applies effective conflict mediation techniques.Records and monitors expenses to ensure conformance to budget constraints. Submits budget recommendations for consideration.Collects and monitors statistics needed for management of operations. Prepares, reviews, maintains, and assists with a variety of related reports, records, and documents.Develops and maintains effective working relationships with all staff. Collaborates with internal and external customers and stakeholders to fulfill the library mission.Responsible for facility and inventory security including general maintenance condition, safety, and security of branches, and liaises with both Library Management and Facilities Maintenance teams to resolve any issues.Responds to customer needs online, over the phone, and in person. Works with individuals to resolve problems. Assists in difficult service interactions, including issues related to library charges.Provides support throughout the hiring process as required. Provides support to Circulation Coordinator and library staff working on the service desk regarding decision making as appropriate.Provides support to Circulation Coordinator with general supervision of Library Students at each branch. This includes taking the lead on employee or performance-related issues involving Library Student staff. Ensures Library System Procedures are maintained: creates and monitors forms as needed; posts on the Intranet and/or shared network drive; communicates with staff in branches to ensure clear understanding and consistency with procedures. Makes recommendations to management for operational changes/improvements. Participates on committees as needed, which may include special projects (e.g., community reads, Santa Claus Parade, etc.) as well as the Joint Health &amp; Safety Committee. Monitors supplies and communicates with appropriate contacts to place orders. Contributes to Health &amp; Safety monitoring, including restocking supplies, first aid kits, updating manuals, etc. Maintains Health &amp; Safety by participating in the Town’s Health &amp; Safety programs and training; follows safety practices; complies with Health &amp; Safety regulations/policies; and maintains awareness of location of supplies, information and contact numbers. Applies knowledge of the Workplace Health &amp; Safety Policy and relevant Occupational Health and Safety legislation to protect the health and safety of employees, and the public as follows:conducts regular inspection of the workplace for unsafe practices and conditions, and ensures a safe and healthy environment; ensures that corrective action has been taken whenever deficiencies are identified; conducts regular safety meetings to review safety conditions and general safety policies for employees; provides information, instructions, and assistance to employees in order to protect the health and safety of all employees; conducts incident investigations and prepares reports and summaries as necessary Stays current in regard to library related technology, practices, and equipment. Willingness to develop new skills and participate in professional development opportunities. Performs other related duties as assigned. The foregoing is intended to outline the general description of the duties and responsibilities for this position. It is not intended nor should it be interpreted as a complete description. Georgina Public Library reserves the right to amend this position description at any time provided that such change does not represent a substantive change in the purpose or essential nature of the position. Qualifications Education and Training: Library Technician’s Diploma, Business Administration diploma, or diploma in another relevant discipline.Experience: Minimum of two (2) years previous library experience, including minimum of 6 months in a Library Assistant position or equivalent.Six months supervisory experience, preferably in a unionized environment. Knowledge:Thorough knowledge of library policies, procedures, practices, and relevant legislation. Competencies:Ability to act as customer service champion.Excellent public relations, problem solving, interpersonal, and organizational skills.Strong leadership and communication skills.Ability to deal effectively with staff through coaching and training.Skill and efficiency in the use of computers and related technologies, including basic proficiency in Excel.Ability to teach others in a patient manner.High ethics and values.Flexibility to work a variety of shifts, including evenings and weekends. Physical Demands and Working ConditionsNormal office conditionsRequirement to travel to various locations.Valid Class 'G' Driver's license and reliable vehicle to use on corporate business.Satisfactory Vulnerable Sector Screening Compensation $75,741 to $89,125 per annum Closes: 4 July, 2023 Georgina Public Library Keswick , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
