ty of our community.We are looking for someone who will collaborate with colleagues and interact with students, faculty, and members of the community, and provide referral and information services such as locating print and digital resources, circulating materials, creating user accounts, providing printing technical support, handling payments, maintaining patron and item records, and performing opening/closing duties.You will report to the University Librarian and receive direction from the Technical Services Supervisor.What you’ll bringSuccessful completion of an accredited 2-year Library Technician program diplomaMinimum four years of related experience in library cataloguing.Information organization and retrieval in a library environmentIntegrated Library Systems (ILS) – (Capilano University Library uses Sierra)Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, Outlook, &amp; PowerPoint)Cataloguing utilities such as MarcEditAcquisitions processes, including placing orders, generating reports, developing purchase requests, and following up with vendorsFor more informationFor more information, please see the complete job description.For more information on the University’s vision visit Envisioning 2030 – Capilano UniversityTake a virtual tour of our campus here: Visit CapU – CapilanoUniversityBenefitsAt Capilano University, we understand that there is more to life than work. That is why we offer comprehensive benefits and support to help you and your family live a balanced life.Take a sneak peek to see what it is like to work at Capilano University.If we could make the application process more accessible for you, or if you have any questions, please contact Christina Neigel at ChristinaNeigel@capilanou.caPosting Detail InformationDays and Hours of WorkWork week: 35 hours per week. Work is conducted primarily on campus, However, CapU offers some flexibility in working conditions and there is an opportunity to request a compressed work schedule for modified work weeks. Further, from May to August, staff have the opportunity to work alternating weeks on-site and remotely.Bridge Period (if applicable)Pay Group18Salary$50,232 (with increments to a max of $56,544 annually) based on a 35-hour work week.UnionMoveUPJob Open Date06/09/2023Job Close Date06/27/2023Open Until FilledNoQuick Link for Postinghttps://jobs-capilanou.peopleadmin.com/postings/5917 Compensation $50,232 (with increments to a max of $56,544 annually) based on a 35-hour work week. Closes: 27 June, 2023 Capilano University North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
